@{
    Layout = "~/_Layout.cshtml";
    Page.Title = "RadioButton Sample";
}
@section banner {<h3>Exploring Bootstrap to format page</h3>}

<blockquote>
    Bootstrap is a css style sheet created as open source. It contains about 10,000 lines of css code.
    Using various aspects of this style sheet can allow us to quickly cia classes block format our
    web page. It will also allow for text alignment, setting up nicely formatted gris diaplays,
    create colour buttons, banners etc.
    Alert allows for color blocking an area plus other stuff. 4 basic colors can be obtained
    by using alert-success, alert-info, alert-warning, alert-danger.
    Default block alignmrnt is left. you can change that using text-xxxx where xxxx is
    left, right or center.
    <br /><br />
    WARNING: Bootstrap is open-source third-party and is subject to change. Thus item that were once
    available may NOT be available in the future. For Bootstrap, if you wish to override a class, it is best to code your own stylesheetand NOT alter the NuGet package if Bootstrap.
</blockquote>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        @*request the 1st 4 blocks of the row*@
        <div class="alert alert-success">
            left text content
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-3 text-md-center text-capitalize text-dark">
        @*request the 1st 3 blocks of the row*@
        <div>Centet text content</div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-5 text-md-right">
        @*request the 1st 5 blocks of the row*@
        <div class="alert alert-danger">
            right text content
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
    <button type="submit" name="theButton" value="submit" class="btn btn-primary">primary</button>&nbsp;&nbsp;
    <button type="submit" name="theButton" value="submit" class="btn btn-light">light</button>&nbsp;&nbsp;
    <button type="submit" name="theButton" value="submit" class="btn btn-dark">dark</button>&nbsp;&nbsp;
    <button type="submit" name="theButton" value="submit" class="btn btn-outline-danger">outline danger</button>&nbsp;&nbsp;
</div>